0quick%20wins.%20But%20this%20time%20he%20has%20seemed%20willing%20to%20risk%20much%20more.%20In%202019%2C%20he%20threatened%20Mexico%20with%205%20percent%20tariffs%20before%20waving%20them%20off.%20Now%2C%20it's%2025%20percent.%20It's%20no%20wonder%20that%20retailers%2C%20home%20builders%2C%20autoworkers%2C%20manufacturers%2C%20auto%20industry%20suppliers%2C%20the%20booze%20industry%20and%20small%20businesses%20all%20urged%20the%20president%20to%20turn%20back.%20The%20duties%20would%20raise%20prices%20for%20Americans%2C%20and%20their%20scope%20is%20immense.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252db17e9-589b-4901-9396-137dc8e47226%5C%22%3ELuis%20Baldomero-Quintana%2C%20economist%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20College%20of%20William%20%26amp%3B%20Mary%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fwhy-trumps-potential-tariffs-are-making-business-owners%2Fid1320118593%3Fi%3D1000685093050%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Trump's%20potential%20tariffs%20are%20making%20business%20owners%20anxious%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20Planet%20Money%20podcast%20hosts%20Wailin%20Wong%20and%20Adrian%20Ma%2C%20Baldomero-Quintana%20said%20there%20will%20be%20three%20ways%20tariff%20uncertainties%20could%20hit%20businesses.%20First%20in%20uncertain%20costs%2C%20second%20in%20uncertain%20retaliations%2C%20and%20third%20in%20forcing%20businesses%20to%20change%20how%20they%20operate%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20could%20hurt%20sales%20and%20global%20competitiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20what%20you%20can%20do%20is%20before%20the%20tariff%20goes%20into%20effect%2C%20you%20go%20and%20make%20a%20gigantic%20purchase%20of%20inputs%20for%2C%20say%2C%20one%20or%20two%20years%20of%20production.%20The%20issue%20is%20it%20costs%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Baldomero-Quintana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e4ea197-65e9-4711-9111-ba5ad64d8b84%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChristopher%20Tang%2C%20professor%20of%20business%20administration%20at%20the%20UCLA%20Anderson%20School%20of%20Management%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fopinion%2Fchina-opinion%2Farticle%2F3300967%2Fus-burning-bridges-china-builds-relationships%3Fmodule%3Dtop_story%26pgtype%3Dsection%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20US%20is%20burning%20bridges%20as%20China%20builds%20relationships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EWhile%20the%20US%20is%20burning%20bridges%20with%20its%20protectionist%20trade%20policies%2C%20China%20is%20building%20bridges%20with%20other%20nations.%20China%20has%20been%20enhancing%20its%20agricultural%20productivity%2C%20advancing%20AI%20and%20technology%2C%20strengthening%20domestic%20innovation%2C%20expanding%20global%20trade%20and%20investing%20in%20Latin%20America.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EDespite%20the%20US%20and%20EU%20imposing%20tariffs%20on%20Chinese%20goods%2C%20China%20is%20leveraging%20its%20port%20investments%20around%20the%20world%20and%20its%20trade%20relationships%20with%20other%20Brics%20countries%20to%20expand%20its%20trade%20with%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Africa%20and%20Latin%20America.%20Since%20the%20trade%20war%20began%20in%202018%2C%20China's%20agricultural%20imports%20from%20the%20US%20have%20declined%2C%20but%20trade%20with%20Latin%20America%20has%20increased%20significantly.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c878763-01ff-4cd2-8c65-044c98f3d7ca%5C%22%3EJohn%20Foley%2C%20Financial%20Times%20Lex%20column%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Ftrump-dump%2Fid1691284824%3Fi%3D1000698169565%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20dump%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20throws%20companies%20into%20a%20state%20of%20grave%20discombobulation.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20what%20we%20know%20about%20companies%20is%20that%20they%20like%20some%20kind%20of%20predictability.%20And%20when%20I've%20been%20talking%20to%20company%20executives%2C%20the%20story%20is%20always%20the%20same.%20It's%20like%20they%20just%20want%20to%20know%20what%20they're%20doing.%20They%20just%20wanna%20know%20where%20to%20put%20their%20assets.%20And%20that%20uncertainty%20is%20the%20most%20damaging%20thing%20for%20companies.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIt's%20not%20bad%20for%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%2C%20traders%20in%20Wall%20Street%20banks%20love%20volatility.%20But%20the%20companies%20themselves%20are%20finding%20it%20very%20hard%20to%20know%20what%20to%20do.%20What%20they%20are%20doing%20is%20making%20noises%20about%20building%20stuff%20in%20the%20US%3A%20opening%20car%20plants%2C%20you%20know%2C%20building%20data%20centres%2C%20whatever%20it%20may%20be.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221b8a73ed-fa4c-47e2-a137-7c6b0d4c426d%5C%22%3EPhil%20Gramm%2C%20economist%20and%20former%20US%20Senator%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fopinion%2Fa-letter-to-trump-from-economists-tariffs-policy-protectionism-economy-9a063b69%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Letter%20on%20Tariffs%20From%20Economists%20to%20Trump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20telling%20that%20the%20Trump%20tariffs%20implemented%20in%20mid-2018%20and%20the%20Biden%20expansion%20of%20those%20tariffs%20didn't%20stop%20the%20secular%20decline%20in%20manufacturing%20employment%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20total%20labor%20force.%20The%20decline%20in%20manufacturing%20employment%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20total%20employment%20is%20being%20driven%20by%20the%20same%20secular%20forces%20that%20caused%20employment%20in%20agriculture%20during%20the%2020th%20century%20to%20fall%20from%2040%25%20to%202%25%20of%20the%20labor%20force%3A%20a%20vast%20increase%20in%20labor%20productivity%20and%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20demand%20for%20manufactured%20products%20relative%20to%20services.%20This%20is%20a%20worldwide%20phenomenon%20occurring%20in%20both%20developed%20and%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227ead8900-e138-4d8f-bb52-a6da7b8845fa%5C%22%3EPaul%20Krugman%2C%20Distinguished%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20at%20the%20Graduate%20Center%20of%20the%20City%20University%20of%20New%20York%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpaulkrugman.substack.com%2Fp%2Fthe-emperors-new-tariffs-small-ugly%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Emperor's%20New%20Tariffs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EAt%20some%20level%20Trump%20is%20aware%20that%20while%20he%20may%20have%20claimed%20victory%20over%20last%20week's%20tariff%20standoff%2C%20everyone%20who%20actually%20knows%20anything%20thinks%20he%20got%20rolled.%20So%20my%20best%20guess%20is%20that%20these%20tariffs%20are%20his%20way%20of%20saying%20%26quot%3BYou%20think%20I%20backed%20down%3F%20Well%2C%20watch%20this!%26quot%3B%20while%20taking%20actions%20that%20look%20big%20to%20the%20uninformed%20but%20not%20so%20much%20to%20people%20who%20can%20crunch%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EIt's%20also%20becoming%20hard%20to%20avoid%20the%20sense%20that%20Trump%20has%20developed%20a%20particular%20animus%20against%20Canada.%20I%20don't%20know%20why%20he%20started%20floating%20the%20idea%20of%20annexing%20our%20neighbor%2C%20but%20the%20fierce%20pushback%20from%20the%20Canadians%20themselves%20and%20the%20ridicule%20he%20has%20received%20at%20home%20seems%20to%20have%20made%20him%20even%20more%20obsessive%20on%20the%20topic.%20And%20this%20may%20in%20part%20explain%20his%20decision%20to%20make%20Canada%20the%20biggest%20target%20of%20his%20mini%20trade%20war.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fse